HEADWORD: Phantascope
<hw>Phan"ta*scope</hw> <pr>(f⟦acr⟧n"t⟦adot⟧*sk⟦omac⟧p)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>fa`ntasma</grk> image +
<ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety> <def>An optical instrument or toy, resembling
the phenakistoscope, and illustrating the same principle; -- called also
<altname>phantasmascope</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

